						               													<description>Set in the near future (as imagined 70 years ago), Zone Runners is the number one show on TV. Each week a team of three contestants tries to complete a Level by running along narrow pathways that hover high in the sky. The better they perform, the more credits they win.&amp;#10;At random intervals gaps appear in these tracks, over which players must jump, or otherwise fall onto the pathway below. &amp;#10;And large mutant creatures, known as Blockers, are also waiting to try to stop their progress.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of this solitaire micro game is to win as many credits as you can!&amp;#10;Each Level consists of 3 tracks (high, mid and low), divided into 7 Zones (cards). The game has 3 Levels, each getting progressively more difficult.&amp;#10;Runners who successfully reach a Level&amp;rsquo;s End Zone are awarded points (credits), depending on the height of track and the Level. A runner who completes one Level can then tackle the next one (hopefully with their other team mates if they also finished it).&amp;#10;You control a team of 3 Runners. You&amp;rsquo;ll be rolling dice and deciding how best to assign them so that each Runner has the best chance of progressing. Runners also have special abilities that can modify their dice score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Zone Runners was voted Best Solitaire Game in the 2017 9-card Nanogame PnP Design Contest.&amp;#10;It was also voted 2nd Best Overall Game.&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#9;&amp;#9;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;EXPANDED EDITION&amp;#10;This edition adds 2 expansions, 4 character ability reference cards, an updated turn tracker card and card backs. &amp;#10;Available from both PNP Arcade https://www.pnparcade.com/products/zone-runners and Randomskill Games https://randomskill.games/product/zone-runners/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
